{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01T5VpEDVijcKDipMSmyX4Ue","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0162hkPGwg8EWg6sFSS8QPTx","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/kubernetes/INCIDENT_REPORT.md","content":"# Incident Report: Informers Miss Events After Receiving DELETE Watch Event\n\n## Summary\n\nKubernetes informers using namespace-scoped watches can permanently miss events after\nreceiving a DELETE event generated by the watch cache's filter logic. The root cause is\nthat the watch cache sends a `PrevObject` with a stale (old) `resourceVersion` in\nsynthetic DELETE events, while both the legacy etcd and etcd3 watchers correctly update\nthe object's resourceVersion to the event's own resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n**Function:** `(*cacheWatcher).sendWatchCacheEvent` (line 874–918)\n**Specific Line:** 892–893\n\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n```\n\nWhen an object is modified so that it no longer matches a namespace-scoped watch filter\n(e.g., it moves to a different namespace, or its labels change so it no longer matches),\nthe watch cache synthesizes a DELETE event for watchers that were tracking the object.\nIt correctly uses `PrevObject` (the old version of the object) as the deleted object.\n\n**The bug:** `PrevObject` is taken from the watch cache's in-memory store (set in\n`watch_cache.go`'s `processEvent` at line 243: `prevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object`).\nThis object retains its **original, old resourceVersion** — the RV it had before the\nmodifying event. The `watchCacheEvent.ResourceVersion` field correctly holds the **event's**\n(current) resourceVersion, but this value is never applied to the `PrevObject` before it\nis sent to clients.\n\n---\n\n## Error Chain\n\n1. **Client-go informer** (`staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go`)\n   establishes a namespace-scoped watch via the API server.\n\n2. **`Cacher.Watch()`** (`cacher.go:292`) creates a `cacheWatcher` filtered by\n   `watchFilterFunction(key, pred)`, which checks `hasPathPrefix(objKey, key)` for\n   namespace scope.\n\n3. The **watch cache reflector** receives a MODIFIED event from the underlying storage\n   (etcd3 or legacy etcd) for an object that moved out of the watched namespace.\n\n4. **`watchCache.processEvent()`** (`watch_cache.go:217–268`) builds a `watchCacheEvent`:\n   - `PrevObject` = previous object fetched from the store — retains **old RV** (e.g., 100)\n   - `ResourceVersion` = **event RV** (e.g., 200)\n\n5. **`Cacher.dispatchEvent()`** (`cacher.go:607`) sends the event to all `cacheWatcher`\n   instances via `cacheWatcher.add()`.\n\n6. **`cacheWatcher.sendWatchCacheEvent()`** (`cacher.go:875`) evaluates the filter:\n   - `curObjPasses = false` (new object is in a different namespace)\n   - `oldObjPasses = true`  (previous object was in the watched namespace)\n   - Constructs: `watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}`\n   - **BUG:** The deep-copied `PrevObject` carries `resourceVersion = \"100\"`, not `\"200\"`.\n\n7. **`reflector.watchHandler()`** (`reflector.go:358`) receives the DELETE event and at\n   line 394 extracts: `newResourceVersion = meta.GetResourceVersion()` → `\"100\"` (stale).\n\n8. At lines 417–418: `*resourceVersion = \"100\"` and `r.setLastSyncResourceVersion(\"100\")`.\n\n9. When the watch connection drops (timeout, network error, etc.), the reflector reopens\n   the watch with `ResourceVersion: \"100\"`.\n\n10. All events in the range `(100, 200]` and beyond may be re-delivered or, if the watch\n    cache history window has advanced past RV=100, the API server returns HTTP 410 Gone,\n    forcing a full re-list. Events generated between RV=100 and the re-list point are\n    permanently missed.\n\n---\n\n## Comparison with Correct Implementations\n\n### etcd3 watcher (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`)\n\nIn `prepareObjs` (line 367–378), the old object is decoded using **`e.rev`** (the event's\nrevision), not the stored object's old revision:\n\n```go\n// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at\n// which it gets deleted.\noldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n```\n\n`decodeObj` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` (line 397) to stamp the\nevent's RV onto the object. The sent DELETE event object always carries the current\nevent's resourceVersion.\n\n### Legacy etcd watcher (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go`)\n\nIn `sendDelete` (line 429–458):\n```go\nnode := *res.PrevNode\nif res.Node != nil {\n    // Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd index for the time at\n    // which it gets deleted. This will allow users to restart the watch at the right index.\n    node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex\n}\nobj, err := w.decodeObject(&node)\n```\n`node.ModifiedIndex` is overwritten with the deletion event's index before decoding.\n\nIn `sendModify` (line 400–401), for filter-based deletes:\n```go\nif err := w.versioner.UpdateObject(oldObj, res.Node.ModifiedIndex); err != nil { ... }\n```\nThe old object is explicitly versioned to the current event's RV.\n\n**The watch cache performs neither of these corrections.**\n\n---\n\n## Affected Components\n\n| Component | File | Role |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| Watch cache filter dispatch | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` | **Bug location**: sends `PrevObject` with stale RV |\n| Watch cache event processing | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` | Stores PrevObject without RV correction |\n| client-go Reflector | `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go` | Trusts the object's RV to resume watches; victim of the bug |\n| etcd3 watcher | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go` | Correct reference implementation |\n| Legacy etcd watcher | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go` | Correct reference implementation |\n\nAll consumers using namespace-scoped watches through the API server watch cache are\naffected. This includes all controllers, operators, and informers in kube-controller-manager,\nkube-scheduler, and any third-party operators.\n\n---\n\n## Remediation\n\nIn `sendWatchCacheEvent` (`cacher.go`), when constructing the synthetic DELETE event for\nthe `!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses` case, the `PrevObject`'s resourceVersion must be\nupdated to `event.ResourceVersion` before it is sent. This mirrors the behavior of both\netcd watchers.\n\nThe fix requires:\n1. DeepCopy `PrevObject` (already done).\n2. Call `meta.Accessor(obj).SetResourceVersion(strconv.FormatUint(event.ResourceVersion, 10))`\n   on the copy, or pass a `Versioner` to `cacheWatcher` and call `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, event.ResourceVersion)`.\n\nThe same correction should be applied to the `event.Type == watch.Deleted` path (line 876),\nwhere `curObjPasses` is always `false` by construction, but `PrevObject` is still sent\nwith its old RV for watchers matching the old object.\n\nReference: etcd3 fix pattern in `prepareObjs` (`etcd3/watcher.go:374`):\n```go\noldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Severity\n\n**High** — Silent data consistency bug affecting all namespace-scoped watch consumers.\nNo error is logged. Controllers may act on stale state or permanently miss update events.\nThe issue is non-deterministic and only manifests after a watch reconnection following\nreceipt of a filter-based DELETE event.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1631,"cache_read_input_tokens":63895,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1631},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f1f0a74-24be-4718-b9fa-cd0683534a46","uuid":"e1f5f767-b550-4e36-862f-450328ebddc6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0162hkPGwg8EWg6sFSS8QPTx","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/kubernetes/INCIDENT_REPORT.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f1f0a74-24be-4718-b9fa-cd0683534a46","uuid":"859c89ac-f4cf-4468-bb05-62e360cff736","timestamp":"2026-04-01T00:59:22.531Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/kubernetes/INCIDENT_REPORT.md","content":"# Incident Report: Informers Miss Events After Receiving DELETE Watch Event\n\n## Summary\n\nKubernetes informers using namespace-scoped watches can permanently miss events after\nreceiving a DELETE event generated by the watch cache's filter logic. The root cause is\nthat the watch cache sends a `PrevObject` with a stale (old) `resourceVersion` in\nsynthetic DELETE events, while both the legacy etcd and etcd3 watchers correctly update\nthe object's resourceVersion to the event's own resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**File:** `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n**Function:** `(*cacheWatcher).sendWatchCacheEvent` (line 874–918)\n**Specific Line:** 892–893\n\n```go\ncase !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n    watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n```\n\nWhen an object is modified so that it no longer matches a namespace-scoped watch filter\n(e.g., it moves to a different namespace, or its labels change so it no longer matches),\nthe watch cache synthesizes a DELETE event for watchers that were tracking the object.\nIt correctly uses `PrevObject` (the old version of the object) as the deleted object.\n\n**The bug:** `PrevObject` is taken from the watch cache's in-memory store (set in\n`watch_cache.go`'s `processEvent` at line 243: `prevObject = previous.(*storeElement).Object`).\nThis object retains its **original, old resourceVersion** — the RV it had before the\nmodifying event. The `watchCacheEvent.ResourceVersion` field correctly holds the **event's**\n(current) resourceVersion, but this value is never applied to the `PrevObject` before it\nis sent to clients.\n\n---\n\n## Error Chain\n\n1. **Client-go informer** (`staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go`)\n   establishes a namespace-scoped watch via the API server.\n\n2. **`Cacher.Watch()`** (`cacher.go:292`) creates a `cacheWatcher` filtered by\n   `watchFilterFunction(key, pred)`, which checks `hasPathPrefix(objKey, key)` for\n   namespace scope.\n\n3. The **watch cache reflector** receives a MODIFIED event from the underlying storage\n   (etcd3 or legacy etcd) for an object that moved out of the watched namespace.\n\n4. **`watchCache.processEvent()`** (`watch_cache.go:217–268`) builds a `watchCacheEvent`:\n   - `PrevObject` = previous object fetched from the store — retains **old RV** (e.g., 100)\n   - `ResourceVersion` = **event RV** (e.g., 200)\n\n5. **`Cacher.dispatchEvent()`** (`cacher.go:607`) sends the event to all `cacheWatcher`\n   instances via `cacheWatcher.add()`.\n\n6. **`cacheWatcher.sendWatchCacheEvent()`** (`cacher.go:875`) evaluates the filter:\n   - `curObjPasses = false` (new object is in a different namespace)\n   - `oldObjPasses = true`  (previous object was in the watched namespace)\n   - Constructs: `watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}`\n   - **BUG:** The deep-copied `PrevObject` carries `resourceVersion = \"100\"`, not `\"200\"`.\n\n7. **`reflector.watchHandler()`** (`reflector.go:358`) receives the DELETE event and at\n   line 394 extracts: `newResourceVersion = meta.GetResourceVersion()` → `\"100\"` (stale).\n\n8. At lines 417–418: `*resourceVersion = \"100\"` and `r.setLastSyncResourceVersion(\"100\")`.\n\n9. When the watch connection drops (timeout, network error, etc.), the reflector reopens\n   the watch with `ResourceVersion: \"100\"`.\n\n10. All events in the range `(100, 200]` and beyond may be re-delivered or, if the watch\n    cache history window has advanced past RV=100, the API server returns HTTP 410 Gone,\n    forcing a full re-list. Events generated between RV=100 and the re-list point are\n    permanently missed.\n\n---\n\n## Comparison with Correct Implementations\n\n### etcd3 watcher (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`)\n\nIn `prepareObjs` (line 367–378), the old object is decoded using **`e.rev`** (the event's\nrevision), not the stored object's old revision:\n\n```go\n// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at\n// which it gets deleted.\noldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n```\n\n`decodeObj` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` (line 397) to stamp the\nevent's RV onto the object. The sent DELETE event object always carries the current\nevent's resourceVersion.\n\n### Legacy etcd watcher (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go`)\n\nIn `sendDelete` (line 429–458):\n```go\nnode := *res.PrevNode\nif res.Node != nil {\n    // Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd index for the time at\n    // which it gets deleted. This will allow users to restart the watch at the right index.\n    node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex\n}\nobj, err := w.decodeObject(&node)\n```\n`node.ModifiedIndex` is overwritten with the deletion event's index before decoding.\n\nIn `sendModify` (line 400–401), for filter-based deletes:\n```go\nif err := w.versioner.UpdateObject(oldObj, res.Node.ModifiedIndex); err != nil { ... }\n```\nThe old object is explicitly versioned to the current event's RV.\n\n**The watch cache performs neither of these corrections.**\n\n---\n\n## Affected Components\n\n| Component | File | Role |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| Watch cache filter dispatch | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go` | **Bug location**: sends `PrevObject` with stale RV |\n| Watch cache event processing | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go` | Stores PrevObject without RV correction |\n| client-go Reflector | `staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache/reflector.go` | Trusts the object's RV to resume watches; victim of the bug |\n| etcd3 watcher | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go` | Correct reference implementation |\n| Legacy etcd watcher | `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go` | Correct reference implementation |\n\nAll consumers using namespace-scoped watches through the API server watch cache are\naffected. This includes all controllers, operators, and informers in kube-controller-manager,\nkube-scheduler, and any third-party operators.\n\n---\n\n## Remediation\n\nIn `sendWatchCacheEvent` (`cacher.go`), when constructing the synthetic DELETE event for\nthe `!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses` case, the `PrevObject`'s resourceVersion must be\nupdated to `event.ResourceVersion` before it is sent. This mirrors the behavior of both\netcd watchers.\n\nThe fix requires:\n1. DeepCopy `PrevObject` (already done).\n2. Call `meta.Accessor(obj).SetResourceVersion(strconv.FormatUint(event.ResourceVersion, 10))`\n   on the copy, or pass a `Versioner` to `cacheWatcher` and call `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, event.ResourceVersion)`.\n\nThe same correction should be applied to the `event.Type == watch.Deleted` path (line 876),\nwhere `curObjPasses` is always `false` by construction, but `PrevObject` is still sent\nwith its old RV for watchers matching the old object.\n\nReference: etcd3 fix pattern in `prepareObjs` (`etcd3/watcher.go:374`):\n```go\noldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Severity\n\n**High** — Silent data consistency bug affecting all namespace-scoped watch consumers.\nNo error is logged. Controllers may act on stale state or permanently miss update events.\nThe issue is non-deterministic and only manifests after a watch reconnection following\nreceipt of a filter-based DELETE event.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
