 both explicitly set the event's revision on the old object before sending.\"\n  },\n  \"remediation\": {\n    \"description\": \"In sendWatchCacheEvent (cacher.go), for the `!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses` case (and the true watch.Deleted case), after DeepCopying PrevObject, update its resourceVersion to event.ResourceVersion using meta.Accessor(obj).SetResourceVersion(strconv.FormatUint(event.ResourceVersion, 10)) or by passing a Versioner to cacheWatcher and calling versioner.UpdateObject(obj, event.ResourceVersion). This mirrors the behavior of both etcd3/watcher.go:374 (decodeObj called with e.rev) and etcd/etcd_watcher.go:441-443 (node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex).\",\n    \"reference_correct_implementations\": [\n      \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go:374 - oldObj decoded with e.rev\",\n      \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go:441-443 - node.ModifiedIndex updated to event index\",\n      \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go:400-401 - versioner.UpdateObject(oldObj, res.Node.ModifiedIndex)\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
